
1. Where to Find Documentation

http://ruby-doc.org/

2. while Loops

Select the core API link for your version of ruby.

Select the "control expressions" link.

3. Return Value of while

nil unless break is used, in which case the value passed to break is used.

4. Return Value of break

nil if no arguments are passed to break, or the value of the argument if an argument is given.

5. Large Numbers

You can write large numbers by using underscores to separate groups of digits.

6. Symbol Syntax

:Claire

7. Default Arguments in the Middle

def my_method(a, b = 2, c = 3, d)
  p [a, b, c, d]
end

my_method(4, 5, 6)

output [4, 5, 3, 6]

8. String Class

http://ruby-doc.org/core-2.5.3/String.html

9. Right Justifying Strings

#rjust

10. Class and Instance Methods

Both methods are on the documentation page for the File class in the Core API section. File::path is a class method, while File#path is an instance method.

